cornflakes.lang

Class FunctionalIterator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • cornflakes.lang.FunctionalIterator<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<T>

    public class FunctionalIterator<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<T>
    The FunctionalIterator class is an iterator implementation which has several convenience functions commonly found in other languages. It is comparable to the new Java 8 Stream structure. The FunctionalIterator is partially immutable. All functions, except for the next() function, return a new iterator and do not modify the original.

      • zip

        public FunctionalIterator<T> zip(FunctionalIterator<T> other)
                          throws IteratorException
        Zips two iterators together. Given two iterators of equal size, this function will return a new iterator which contains the first item in the first iterator followed by the first item in the second iterator, followed by the second item in the first iterator followed by the second item in the second iterator, etc.
        Parameters:
        other - The iterator to zip the current iterator with
        Returns:
        A new iterator, which contains the zip of the current iterator the given iterator
        Throws:
        IteratorException - If either iterator is empty, or if the iterators have an inequal length
